ğŸ”¹ Binary Conversion Rule (Decimal â†’ Binary)

To convert a decimal number into binary, follow these steps:

1 > Divide the number by 2.
2 > Write down the remainder (0 if even, 1 if odd).
3 > Update the quotient (ignore the remainder).
4 > Repeat until quotient becomes 0.
5 > Read the remainders from bottom to top â†’ thatâ€™s your binary.

Example: Convert 47 into Binary

Step	Number Ã· 2	Quotient	Remainder
1	47 Ã· 2	23	1
2	23 Ã· 2	11	1
3	11 Ã· 2	5	1
4	5 Ã· 2	2	1
5	2 Ã· 2	1	0
6	1 Ã· 2	0	1

ğŸ‘‰ Now read remainders from bottom to top:
47 (decimal) = 101111 (binary)

âœ… Shortcut Rule:

Even number â†’ binary ends with 0.
Odd number â†’ binary ends with 1.

